### getInstrProfRecord() {#a8a83ecab002375cf09cf04f12470bf0e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; InstrProfRecord &gt; IndexedInstrProfReader::getInstrProfRecord (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> FuncName, uint64&#95;t FuncHash, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> DeprecatedFuncName=&quot;&quot;, uint64&#95;t &#42; MismatchedFuncSum=nullptr)</>}>
Return the <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/namedinstrprofrecord">NamedInstrProfRecord</a> associated with FuncName and FuncHash.

When return a hash&#95;mismatch error and MismatchedFuncSum is not nullptr, the sum of all counters in the mismatched function will be set to MismatchedFuncSum. If there are multiple instances of mismatched functions, MismatchedFuncSum returns the maximum. If <code>FuncName</code> is not found, try to lookup <code>DeprecatedFuncName</code> to handle profiles built by older compilers.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/profiledata/instrprofreader-h/#l00815">815</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/profiledata/instrprofreader-h">InstrProfReader.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprofreader-cpp/#l01494">1494</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprofreader-cpp">InstrProfReader.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### getSymtab() {#a539ed03ca959115bcc032f7e7d655d42}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>InstrProfSymtab &amp; IndexedInstrProfReader::getSymtab ()</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Return the PGO symtab.

There are three different readers: Raw, Text, and Indexed profile readers. The first two types of readers are used only by llvm-profdata tool, while the indexed profile reader is also used by llvm-cov tool and the compiler ( backend or frontend). Since creating PGO symtab can create significant runtime and memory overhead (as it touches data for the whole program), <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instrprofsymtab">InstrProfSymtab</a> for the indexed profile reader should be created on demand and it is recommended to be only used for dumping purpose with llvm-proftool, not with the compiler.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/profiledata/instrprofreader-h/#l00871">871</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/profiledata/instrprofreader-h">InstrProfReader.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprofreader-cpp/#l01473">1473</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/profiledata/instrprofreader-cpp">InstrProfReader.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
